id: pm-tobi
title: Default-safety policy for destructive pm commands (gc keeps delete-by-default; add pm delete --dry-run)
description: "Resolves pm-5k2w L10. Question: pm gc deletes by default (dry_run:false) while normalize/update-many default to dry-run; pm delete had no preview/dry-run. Decision: (1) KEEP pm gc deleting by default — it is an explicit, opt-in maintenance command a user/agent runs deliberately, output already lists removed targets, and --dry-run is available for preview; flipping its default would be a breaking behavior change for scripts and CI. Mitigation: make the help text state plainly that gc removes files by default and document --dry-run prominently. (2) normalize/update-many KEEP dry-run-by-default — they rewrite many items in place, so preview-first is the safe default. (3) ADD `pm delete --dry-run` (additive, non-breaking) so the single-item destructive path has a preview that reports what would be deleted without mutating; pm delete remains immediate without the flag (existing behavior preserved). Rationale: align safety affordances (every destructive command can be previewed) without changing any existing default behavior."
type: Decision
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,cli,decision,default-safety,dogfood
created_at: "2026-05-23T17:08:54.664Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T18:17:52.591Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: gc help documents delete-by-default + --dry-run; pm delete gains a non-mutating --dry-run that reports the target; no existing default behavior changed; regression tests cover delete --dry-run.
parent: pm-5k2w
resolution: "Implemented default-safety decision: kept gc delete-by-default with clearer help and added non-mutating pm delete --dry-run."
expected_result: Destructive commands retain existing defaults but have clear preview affordances and docs.
actual_result: pm delete dry-run previews target without history/item mutation; gc help clarifies default delete; contracts/completions/tests/manual dogfood/full release gate passed.
